{{nihongo|'''Notojima'''|能登島|Noto-jima}} is a volcanic island in the [[:ja:七尾湾|Nanao Bay]] portion of the [[Sea of Japan]], less than 500 meters off the coast of the [[Ishikawa Prefecture|Shimane]] prefecture in [[Japan]]. Notojima Island is administered as part of [[Nanao, Ishikawa|Nanao]] city. The two bridges connecting '''Notojima''' to the mainland are trisecting [[:ja:七尾湾|Nanao Bay]] into Nanao-North, Nanao-West and Nanao-Nambu bays. ==History== *1982 - {{nihongo|'''Notojima big bridge'''|能登島大橋|Notojima ohashi}} is complete (southern bridge) *1999 - {{nihongo|'''Twin Bridge Noto'''|ツインブリッジ能登|Tsuinburijji Noto}} is complete (northern bridge) *October 1, 2004 - the [[Notojima, Ishikawa|Notojima town]] has become the part of the [[Nanao, Ishikawa|Nanao]] city and [[:ja:能登半島国定公園|Noto-Hanto Quazi-National Park]]. *March 25, 2007 - [[2007 Noto earthquake]] of 6.9 [[Moment magnitude scale]] happened. ==See also== *[[Notojima, Ishikawa]] *This article incorporates material from Japanese Wikipedia page [[:ja:能登島|能登島]], accessed 10 January 2017 {{Commons category|Notoshima}}
==References== {{reflist}} {{Authority control}} [[Category:Islands of Ishikawa Prefecture]] [[Category:Islands of the Sea of Japan]] {{ishikawa-geo-stub}}

